					<p>Consider if:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Uncorrectable uterine abnormality</li>
						<li>Multiple losses despite normal embryos</li>
						<li>Medical conditions making pregnancy dangerous</li>
					</ul>
					<a href="/treatments/third-party/" class="option-link">Learn about surrogacy ‚Üí</a>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2>Emotional Support</h2>

			<p>Recurrent loss is emotionally devastating. Taking care of your mental health is just as important as physical treatment.</p>

			<div class="support-options">
				<div class="support-item">
					<span class="support-icon">üí¨</span>
					<div>
						<strong>Counseling</strong>
						<p>Individual or couples therapy with someone experienced in pregnancy loss</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="support-item">
					<span class="support-icon">üë•</span>
					<div>
						<strong>Support Groups</strong>
						<p>RESOLVE, local pregnancy loss support groups, online communities</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="support-item">
					<span class="support-icon">‚è∏Ô∏è</span>
					<div>
						<strong>Taking Breaks</strong>
						<p>It's okay to pause between attempts‚Äîhealing takes time</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="callout callout-success">
				<span class="callout-icon">üíö</span>
				<div class="callout-content">
					<strong>There is hope:</strong> Even after 3 unexplained losses, the chance of a successful next pregnancy is 60-75% without any treatment. With appropriate treatment for identified causes, success rates can be even higher.
				</div>
